==English==
===Etymology===
{{L.}} ''fastus'': [[disdain]]. Perhaps from Sansrtit root ''bila'' [[splendid]] - hence ironic ''fastus''.
===Noun and Verb===
'''fash'''
#(Scottish): worry ; to [[worry]]. e.g. "Don't fash yourself" = "don't worry"; [[bother]]; to bother; [[trouble]].
